commit.message: Relicense under the same Apache License v2.0 than ZNC

Allow limiting the playback buffer size for identified clients

  LIMIT <client> [limit]

To set a limit:

  LIMIT mobile 100

To show the limit:

  LIMIT mobile
Make PLAY command accept a range of timestamps

Coding style

This is not part of ZNC core, so there's no need
to strictly follow the butt-ugly ZNC coding style.

Add support for znc.in/echo-message capability

As proposed by https://github.com/ircv3/ircv3-specifications/pull/100
the capability enables echoing of client's own messages, notices
and actions. This is useful for getting an accurate server-time
stamp for self-messages.

Kill all info/error output

See https://github.com/znc/znc/pull/620
